overview: The user initiated a project to build a sleep questionnaire
  application, focusing on database integration and an admin dashboard. After
  evaluating the existing codebase, it was determined that a database for
  storing questionnaire responses, a CSV export feature, and an authenticated
  admin dashboard were the primary missing components. The user opted for a
  simple password-based authentication and a combined set of demographic data
  (year of birth, sex, zipcode, weight, height). The implementation involved
  updating data models and validation, creating API routes for data persistence
  and retrieval, and developing the admin dashboard. A key decision was to
  refactor the authentication system to leverage Next.js middleware,
  streamlining route protection and simplifying session management. The database
  was set up using NeonDB with Prisma, and the entire functionality was tested
  through questionnaire submission, admin login, and CSV download, confirming
  successful data flow and access.
